p: The statistical analysis of the data was performed using the SPSS 20.0 software. The results obtained are expressed as mean Â± standard deviation. Differences between groups were assessed using one-way ANOVA followed by Duncan post hoc test. P-value was done using the student t- test. A p value of less than 0.05 was considered as significant. The normality of data was tested by the Shapiro-Wilk Test and the relationships between different parameters highlighted by the correlation coefficient of Bravais Pearson.
